thread.title: Saints planning to start Drew Brees against Cowboys
thread.title_full: Saints planning to start Drew Brees against Cowboys | Dallas Morning News

author: Jon Machota
title: Saints planning to start Drew Brees against Cowboys
text:
IRVING -- Saints coach Sean Payton says he expects quarterback Drew Brees to start Sunday night against the Cowboys.
Brees, who has a bruised throwing shoulder, missed the Saints game last Sunday.
Cowboys weakside linebacker Sean Lee said the team has expected all along that Brees would be the starter.
"Being the quarterback he is, obviously it'll be an incredible challenge," Lee said. "He's a Hall of Fame-type of guy. We've played him before. He's an unbelievable quarterback and an unbelievable challenge and we knew with a guy like that, he's fought through injuries before, so we knew he probably would be playing."
In seven career games against the Cowboys, Brees is 4-3, throwing for 2,421 yards, 18 touchdowns and five interceptions. In last year's 38-17 loss to Dallas, Brees was 32 of 44 for 340 yards, two touchdowns and one interception.
"It doesn't really matter what quarterback is playing," Cowboys defensive tackle Tyrone Crawford said. "For us on the D-line, it's simple, we just play our ball out there and focus on us and do what we have to do and read our keys and everything should work out."
